SENATE BILL DRS15207-LRa-112
Short Title: Juvenile Justice Workforce Fix/Funds. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Bradley, Theodros, and Smith (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT AWARDING A LEGISLATIVE SALARY INCREASE FOR JUVENILE JUSTICE
3 STAFF AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS FOR THAT PURPOSE.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.(a) Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General Fund
6 to the Department of Public Safety, Division of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, the
7 sum of ten million four hundred thousand dollars ($10,400,000) in recurring funds for the
8 2025-2026 fiscal year and the sum of fourteen million one hundred thousand dollars
9 ($14,100,000) in recurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be allocated for employee salary
10 increases as awarded by Section 2 of this act.
11 SECTION 1.(b) Of the funds appropriated in subsection (a) of this section, the sum
12 of three million nine hundred thousand dollars ($3,900,000) shall be allocated to reduce salary
13 compression in connection with these increases.
14 SECTION 2.(a) Effective for the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium, the following annual
15 salary schedules shall be in effect for Youth Counselor Technicians, Youth Services Behavioral
16 Specialists, and Youth Counselors in the Division of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency
17 Prevention:
